  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The [test documentation](http://www.ethdocs.org/en/latest/contracts-and-transactions/ethereum-tests/index.html) feels somewhat misplaced in the generic Homestead docs being too detailed for the end user/dapp dev and also being too hidden in the tree structure there.\r\n\r\nPlacing the documentation files directly here in a ``docs`` folder and hosting it separately (probably also on ReadTheDocs) from the Homestead docs would greatly encourage pull requests for documentation updates and enhancements and - that would be my hope - significantly improve documentation quality. Atm this \"feels\" too far away and very few people find the way over to make a pull for a subfolder file in the homestead docs repo.\r\n\r\nIf there is interest/support for this change, I could do the preparations for it.",
